# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Second Brain Generator — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` (done automatically by `node installer.mjs`).
# `.env` is gitignored: it will NEVER be committed.
#
# Layout: the SECRETS YOU FILL IN are at the top; everything below the
# "ADVANCED / OPTIONAL" divider has working defaults you can ignore.
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 🔑 SECRETS TO FILL IN
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google Gemini API key — required ONLY if you use the Gemini embedder (the
# historical default). The installer no longer forces it: if you picked the
# "everything on your machine" option (in-process) or another provider, leave it
# empty and see the "Embedder choice" section further down (EMBEDDING_PROVIDER).
# Free key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GOOGLE_GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Golden-source Notion tokens (one per connected source) also land HERE, e.g.
# `NOTION_TOKEN_PASC=ntn_…`. You don't add them by hand: the `/golden-source`
# skill writes the placeholder line and opens this file for you to paste the
# token. The token is referenced by NAME only (never committed, never in chat).


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ⚙️  ADVANCED / OPTIONAL — working defaults; most users never touch these.
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Embedding quota safety nets (defaults in rag/src/lib/config.ts) ───
# Hard cap on embedding requests per day (runaway safety net):
# MAX_EMBED_REQUESTS_PER_DAY=7600
# Quota reserve dedicated to searches (search never blocked by indexing):
# QUERY_RESERVE=50

# ── Relocatable Engine paths (engine-packaging Phase 0) ──────────────
# By default the Engine finds the vault, its cache and this .env by their
# historical position relative to the brain folder — leave these UNSET and
# nothing changes. Set them only to run the Engine from a different layout
# (a relative value resolves against the working directory; absolute is taken
# as-is).
# VAULT_DIR=vault                 # where the notes live (default: <brain>/vault)
# CACHE_DIR=rag/.cache            # the index cache (default: <brain>/rag/.cache)
# SBG_ENV_PATH=.env               # this very file (default: <brain>/.env)

# ── Embedder choice (default: native Gemini above) ───────────────────
# To use a provider OTHER than Gemini, without touching the code (ADR 0007):
# a SINGLE "OpenAI-compatible" adapter covers OpenAI, Azure, an enterprise
# gateway, Mistral… AND LOCAL via Ollama (no key, nothing leaves the machine).
# Just change these variables — automatic reindex on swap (identity stamp).
#
#   EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=openai-compatible
#   EMBEDDING_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1   # local Ollama (no key)
#   EMBEDDING_API_KEY=                             # empty locally; sk-... for OpenAI/Azure
#   EMBEDDING_MODEL_NAME=bge-m3                     # model name on the provider side
#   EMBEDDING_DIMENSION=1024                        # model dimension (index invalidation key)
#
# ⚠️ The dimension MUST match the chosen model (bge-m3 → 1024,
#    text-embedding-3-small → 1536, EmbeddingGemma → 768…). A wrong number
#    would stamp the index incorrectly. Leave EMBEDDING_PROVIDER empty/absent to stay on Gemini.

# ── FULLY-LOCAL, NOTHING TO INSTALL variant ("Gemma inside") ─────────
# The embedder runs INSIDE the RAG's Node process (Transformers.js + ONNX): no key,
# no cloud, NO separate app (not even Ollama). The weights download once on first
# use, then everything is offline. Just set:
#
#   EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=in-process
#   # EMBEDDING_MODEL_NAME=onnx-community/embeddinggemma-300m-ONNX  # default (768 dim)
#   # EMBEDDING_DIMENSION=768                                       # default
#
# Another ONNX model is possible (e.g. EMBEDDING_MODEL_NAME=Xenova/bge-m3 + EMBEDDING_DIMENSION=1024).
# No URL or key here: the adapter calls the model directly, without HTTP.
